<p>In my application.conf are two datasources configured:</p>  <pre><code>db.default.driver=com.mysql.jdbc.Driver db.default.url="jdbc:mysql://IP/db" db.default.username=user db.default.password=pw db.default.jndiName=DefaultDS  db.mydb.driver=com.mysql.jdbc.Driver db.mydb.url="jdbc:mysql://AnotherIP/sameDB" db.mydb.username=user db.mydb.password=pw db.mydb.jndiName=MydbDS  jpa.default=defaultPersistenceUnit jpa.mydb=mydbPersistenceUnit </code></pre>  <p>The persistance.xml has the same entries for both persistance units (default, mydb). Now I'm trying to use the mydb config like this:</p>  <pre><code>JPA.em("mydb") </code></pre>  <p>It works for a simple read query, but not with <em>JPA.em("mydb").persist</em>, e.g. no data are written and no error is thrown. When using <em>JPA.em().persist</em> there is no problem at all. Is there something I miss? How could a debug this? I'm starting the application with the Activator UI.</p>